Class JSONArray

java.lang.Object
ru.introguzzle.parsers.common.util.DelegatingArray<Object>
ru.introguzzle.parsers.common.util.UntypedArray
ru.introguzzle.parsers.json.entity.JSONArray
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Iterable<Object>, Collection<Object>, Consumer<Visitor<JSONArray>>, List<Object>, SequencedCollection<Object>, Visitable<JSONArray,Visitor<JSONArray>>, JSONStringConvertable
public class JSONArray extends UntypedArray implements JSONStringConvertable, Visitable<JSONArray,Visitor<JSONArray>>, Serializable
Represents a JSON array as a list of objects.

This class extends ArrayList to provide a structure for JSON arrays, enabling easy serialization to and from JSON strings. It implements the JSONStringConvertable interface.

    • toJSONObject

      public JSONObject toJSONObject(@NotNull @NotNull Function<Object,String> keyExtractor, @Nullable @Nullable BiFunction<Object,String,String> remappingFunction)
      Converts this JSONArray to a JSONObject using a specified key extractor function and an optional remapping function for handling duplicate keys.
      Parameters:
      keyExtractor - a function that extracts a key from each element in the JSONArray. This key will be used in the resulting JSONObject.
      remappingFunction - an optional function that allows for custom remapping of keys when a duplicate key is detected in the JSONObject. This function takes the current value and the existing key as parameters, and should return the new key to be used in the JSONObject. If no remapping function is provided or if no duplicate key is found, the original key is used.
      Returns:
      a JSONObject constructed from the elements of this JSONArray, with keys generated by the keyExtractor and remapped as necessary by the remappingFunction.
